WEBVTT

00:19.728 --> 00:21.013
Wow.

00:21.771 --> 00:22.806
You look great.

00:23.815 --> 00:27.273
Thanks.
Never hurts to change it up a little bit.

00:27.444 --> 00:28.684
Except for the ring.

00:28.862 --> 00:33.105
Never gonna take that off.
It's my sparkly little ball and chain.

00:34.159 --> 00:36.445
Any second thoughts
about your girls' night out?

00:36.619 --> 00:39.702
Clark, my swinging single days
have swung.

00:39.873 --> 00:42.364
It's just all this wedding stuff
is very wedding-y.

00:42.542 --> 00:44.078
I never thought I'd be that gal.

00:44.461 --> 00:48.079
CHLOE: Ahem. Lois?
-I think there's something missing.

00:48.256 --> 00:52.920
Ta-da! Your bachelorette superpower-up.

00:53.178 --> 00:55.510
Not bad.
I thought I'd be spending the night...

00:55.680 --> 00:59.172
...cuffed to a blowup doll
while wearing a dog collar.

00:59.350 --> 01:00.385
So with this thing...

01:00.560 --> 01:02.926
-...I will be drinking free all night long.
-Yes, she will.

01:03.104 --> 01:04.719
[WOMEN GIGGLING]

01:05.440 --> 01:07.021
Oh. Got it.

01:07.192 --> 01:11.105
After all the years that I've known you,
I don't think I've seen you this happy.

01:11.321 --> 01:13.812
Well, it wouldn't be the same
without you being here.

01:14.365 --> 01:17.027
| just wish I could freeze this moment
in time forever.

01:17.202 --> 01:18.738
Me too.

01:18.912 --> 01:22.245
Unfortunately, the limo is here,
so we should go.

01:22.415 --> 01:24.246
Oh, but before we do, a toast.

01:24.417 --> 01:28.205
Oh, right. A toast. Sorry.
Forgot that one.

01:31.341 --> 01:32.751
To the bride and groom.

01:36.846 --> 01:38.882
You know, to friends.

01:39.974 --> 01:45.264
You two amazing people have been the
best friends I could have ever asked for.

01:45.563 --> 01:49.522
And we want you to know...

01:49.692 --> 01:51.523
...that we are here for you...

01:51.945 --> 01:53.856
...to support you...

01:54.030 --> 01:57.147
...as you begin
your happily-ever-after adventure.

01:57.951 --> 02:02.945
And tonight
is all about celebrating you.

02:04.290 --> 02:06.542
And I hope you boys have fun
tonight...

02:06.709 --> 02:08.700
...but don't do anything I wouldn't do.

02:08.878 --> 02:10.618
OLIVER:
No. No, we wouldn't do that.

02:11.589 --> 02:13.500
Okay. To the bride and groom.

02:13.675 --> 02:15.961
-Cheers.
-Cheers.

02:18.638 --> 02:20.629
[ALL LAUGHING]

02:25.228 --> 02:27.219
[CRUNCHING]

02:47.667 --> 02:49.077
[G ROANS]

02:51.379 --> 02:52.619
[LEMUR CHITTERING]

03:03.141 --> 03:04.631
[CRASHING]

03:15.653 --> 03:16.904
[MOANS]

03:25.455 --> 03:26.786
Chloe?

03:26.956 --> 03:28.787
Clark?

03:30.168 --> 03:31.248
What did you do?

03:34.797 --> 03:36.128
[G ROANS]

03:40.261 --> 03:42.343
What did we do?

03:42.847 --> 03:45.714
[LEMUR CHITTERING]

04:47.036 --> 04:48.116
CLARK:
Stay!

04:48.288 --> 04:51.701
Okay, he can just hang tight in there
while we ﬁgure this out.

04:51.874 --> 04:53.865
[LEMUR CHITTERING]

04:55.211 --> 04:57.497
-You don't think that we—?
-Exchanged vows?

04:57.672 --> 04:58.752
-I mean--
-Said "I do"?

04:58.923 --> 05:00.629
-Both—
-Did the deed? Oh, God.

05:01.092 --> 05:04.926
Don't say the word "consummate."
The answer has to be no.

05:08.141 --> 05:10.348
Okay.
What if these are just costumes?

05:10.560 --> 05:12.266
Right. We went to a costume party...

05:12.437 --> 05:15.600
...dressed like the top
of a wedding cake? Clark.

05:21.696 --> 05:24.563
Looks like things
got a little out of control.

05:25.491 --> 05:29.154
Okay, before we go DEFCON 1
on the stag party snafu...

05:29.329 --> 05:32.913
...let's just take a step back. Whoa.

05:33.082 --> 05:35.573
I can't, Chloe. l have no memory
of what happened...

05:35.752 --> 05:37.583
...which is weird, because alcohol--

05:37.754 --> 05:40.166
Yeah, well,
my memory Etch A Sketch is blank too.

05:41.632 --> 05:44.715
Must be more than champagne
in these bottles.

05:46.971 --> 05:48.711
I didn't realize this was a gift.

05:48.890 --> 05:51.302
"Congrats, Clark.
You deserve a real party.

05:51.476 --> 05:53.137
Hugs, Zatanna."

05:54.187 --> 05:56.178
She must have put a spell on these.

05:56.356 --> 05:58.142
Complete with a memory-erase.

05:58.316 --> 06:01.228
If Zatanna's mind-wipe affected you,
it could've affected Oliver.

06:01.402 --> 06:02.733
It could have affected all of us.

06:02.904 --> 06:03.939
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

06:04.113 --> 06:05.364
Lois.

06:05.531 --> 06:07.487
Where's your phone?

06:08.284 --> 06:09.945
Lois?

06:10.119 --> 06:12.405
Yes, this is Clark Kent.

06:12.914 --> 06:15.326
You have my wallet downtown?

06:21.255 --> 06:22.870
If your wallet was on the hood...

06:23.049 --> 06:25.506
...that throws
the costume party theory out.

06:30.848 --> 06:32.179
There's no sign of a driver.

06:32.350 --> 06:35.137
You know,
maybe there's a number we can call.

06:38.147 --> 06:39.853
-Whoa.
CLARK: Chloe, look.

06:40.024 --> 06:42.982
I got a text message from last night.
And it's from Lois.

06:43.152 --> 06:45.814
It says, "I just need more time."

06:48.825 --> 06:50.907
What if she doesn't wanna be found?

06:51.077 --> 06:53.409
What if all this got to her
and pushed her away?

06:53.579 --> 06:59.324
Clark, okay, all of the taffeta and lace
and goofy traditions in the world...

06:59.502 --> 07:01.163
...are not gonna give Lois jitters.

07:01.337 --> 07:02.918
This is not the ﬁrst time...

07:03.089 --> 07:06.081
...that she has bailed
when things got real between us.

07:06.259 --> 07:08.921
First time I kissed her she left town.

07:09.095 --> 07:11.586
When she found out l was the Blur,
she went to Egypt.

07:11.764 --> 07:14.597
Clark, your relationship
is at a different level right now.

07:14.767 --> 07:18.680
Not to mention the fact that Lois knows
that you are the proverbial one.

07:18.855 --> 07:21.722
And besides that,
weddings just aren't that scary.

07:22.191 --> 07:24.056
I hope you're right.

07:25.528 --> 07:27.769
Are those Emil's pants?

07:28.865 --> 07:31.231
-Yeah, I found it in the back seat.
-What's that?

07:31.409 --> 07:34.242
It looks like half
of a wedding certiﬁcate.

07:34.412 --> 07:36.778
Missing one of the names.

07:39.750 --> 07:43.083
Holy matrimony. That's my signature.

07:44.464 --> 07:46.045
Clark, we really are married.

07:47.258 --> 07:48.873
Emil. He wasn't drinking.

07:49.051 --> 07:52.043
He'll have answers.
I'll call you after I ﬁnd our friends.

07:52.346 --> 07:54.632
Oh! Clark.

07:55.975 --> 07:57.636
Are you okay?

07:58.936 --> 08:01.769
Chloe, this killer headache
is affecting my abilities.

08:01.939 --> 08:03.930
This might be more difﬁcult
than I thought.

08:04.108 --> 08:06.394
[GIRLS CHUCKLING]

08:09.989 --> 08:11.820
| just got an idea of where to start.

08:11.991 --> 08:13.947
Excuse me.

08:14.118 --> 08:15.699
[MAN SINGING INDISTINCTLY
OVER PHONE]

08:15.870 --> 08:17.360
Where did you get those shirts?

08:18.581 --> 08:21.163
[SINGING OVER PHONE]
I had a gun in my hand

08:21.334 --> 08:25.623
Drinkin' forty pounds for dinner
Till I met a big man

08:25.796 --> 08:26.831
And the man said

08:27.006 --> 08:28.587
One night and he's already famous.

08:31.844 --> 08:35.257
Emil always was an overachiever.
Why don't you go take care of that...

08:35.431 --> 08:38.594
...and I'm gonna call Oliver,
and I'll meet you at the Watchtower.

08:38.768 --> 08:40.178
Okay.

08:41.729 --> 08:44.141
[INTRO TO SWANK'S "HOW DO WE DO"
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

08:49.028 --> 08:50.359
[SINGING]
Let me tell you something

08:50.530 --> 08:54.443
I was a hard drinkin' sinner
And I had blood on my hands

08:55.117 --> 08:58.860
I was a hard drinkin' sinner
I had a gun in my hand

08:59.038 --> 09:03.372
Drinkin' forty pounds for dinner
Till I met a big man

09:03.543 --> 09:04.623
[CHUCKLES]

09:04.794 --> 09:07.957
And the man said
How do we do

09:08.130 --> 09:10.542
-Well, I pulled a lot of triggers
-Baby

09:10.716 --> 09:14.300
Shot a lotta good men
Broke a lotta hearts

09:14.470 --> 09:17.086
-Oh, yeah
-Hearts that never will mend

09:17.265 --> 09:19.221
-But now I'm at the station
-That's my girl

09:19.392 --> 09:21.053
-And I have made a new friend
-Oh

09:21.227 --> 09:24.560
And my friend says
How do we do

09:24.730 --> 09:28.348
BOTH: How do we do
How do we do

09:28.526 --> 09:29.561
CHORUS:
How do we do

09:29.735 --> 09:34.149
BOTH: Oh, the man said
How do we do

09:34.323 --> 09:38.407
And I'm feelin' reborn
I feel I'm anew

09:38.578 --> 09:43.038
'Cause the man said
How do we do

09:46.043 --> 09:48.159
Shake it, baby.

09:48.504 --> 09:51.086
EMIL:
Oh, yeah

09:52.174 --> 09:55.211
The one guy I counted on
remaining sober.

10:01.601 --> 10:02.841
Do we know each other?

10:04.186 --> 10:06.268
So you did have fun last night.

10:09.775 --> 10:12.357
I'm looking for the girl
that came with me last night.

10:12.528 --> 10:14.234
She insulted you more than once.

10:14.405 --> 10:18.364
She was there when I dropped you off
but was gone when I picked you up.

10:20.870 --> 10:22.110
At the Chapel of Love.

10:22.538 --> 10:26.372
CHORUS: The man said
How do we do

10:26.542 --> 10:28.248
And I'm feelin' reborn

10:28.419 --> 10:32.378
TESS:
Honey pie, come on over here.

10:32.548 --> 10:36.086
CHORUS: How do we do
How do we do

10:36.260 --> 10:38.967
COP: Emil Hamilton,
can you step off the stage, please?

10:39.138 --> 10:42.255
We got questions about an armored car
that was stolen last night.

10:42.433 --> 10:45.925
Thank you very much, gentleman,
l plead innocent to all charges.

10:46.103 --> 10:48.139
-l'm but a humble entertainer.
-Funny.

10:48.314 --> 10:51.647
You can tell the judge
how you made it vanish into thin air.

10:51.817 --> 10:53.603
Into thin air.

10:53.778 --> 10:56.736
TESS:
Oh, Clarkie. Oh.

10:56.906 --> 10:59.022
There's only one person that I know...

10:59.200 --> 11:02.613
...that can make an armored car adios
in seconds.

11:02.787 --> 11:03.822
[MAKES POPPING SOUND]

11:08.626 --> 11:10.241
[WOMAN MUMBLING]

11:10.419 --> 11:12.751
WOMAN:
Take those.

11:26.060 --> 11:27.596
Clark.

11:28.979 --> 11:31.561
Hey. Hey, watch it, buster.

11:31.732 --> 11:33.393
-Sorry.
-Roll.

11:33.943 --> 11:35.274
Hi.

11:35.444 --> 11:36.980
Morning.

11:37.196 --> 11:40.108
-Sorry.
-Good morning. It's okay.

11:41.117 --> 11:44.951
Whoa, my head is pounding
like a mosh pit...

11:45.329 --> 11:49.618
...and my mouth tastes like armpit. Hmm.

11:50.126 --> 11:52.082
Hey.

11:55.923 --> 11:57.754
What happened?

11:57.925 --> 11:59.836
I think the jury's still out...

12:00.010 --> 12:02.877
...but I'd say we just survived
the world's greatest bachelor party.

12:03.055 --> 12:04.090
[CHUCKLES]

12:04.265 --> 12:08.258
Ugh, ha.
No offense, but speak for yourself.

12:08.436 --> 12:10.802
My dream soiree
would end waking up...

12:10.980 --> 12:17.146
...with someone a little taller, darker
and a different kind of handsome.

12:17.486 --> 12:21.024
Well, no surprise there. How the hell
did we end up here, anyway?

12:21.240 --> 12:23.322
LOIS:
Oh, I have no idea.

12:23.826 --> 12:28.160
But in that green getup of yours, we're
gonna stand out like a hooker in church.

12:28.330 --> 12:30.821
-What?
-Heh. Ha-ha-ha.

12:31.000 --> 12:33.161
-Yeah.
-What is this?

12:33.377 --> 12:34.492
[CHUCKLES]

12:35.671 --> 12:38.834
You know what? I thought my drunken
blackout days were behind me--

12:39.008 --> 12:41.545
Tell me about it.
Lanes can usually hold our liquor...

12:41.761 --> 12:44.844
...but I don't have a single memory
of my big night.

12:45.848 --> 12:49.682
So we'd better drop a line
to Clark and Chloe. They'll be worried.

12:52.313 --> 12:54.019
Oopsie. I just realized something.

12:54.190 --> 12:57.353
When I changed my pants,
I forgot all the important things.

12:57.860 --> 13:00.146
Yeah. My cell phone's gonzo too.

13:00.321 --> 13:03.188
A bummer, since this isn't
Mister Rogers' Neighborhood.

13:03.365 --> 13:06.027
OLIVER: It's okay. It's all right.
You know what we're gonna do?

13:06.202 --> 13:08.864
We're gonna ﬁnd one of those
phone booths of yours...

13:09.038 --> 13:11.370
...and call Clark,
everything's gonna be great.

13:11.540 --> 13:13.076
Can't call Clark.

13:14.710 --> 13:17.873
Sometimes, I don't understand—
What--? What's the problem, huh?

13:21.425 --> 13:23.211
My engagement ring is gone.

13:34.939 --> 13:37.931
Any luck on that armored car
it looks like I stole?

13:38.108 --> 13:41.566
We don't have much time.
Emil is in prison now because of me.

13:44.740 --> 13:46.901
Still searching for missing vehicles.

13:47.076 --> 13:50.910
God, I feel terrible, I'm the one that
convinced him to drink that champagne.

13:51.080 --> 13:54.743
Not your fault, Tess. Lois? Oliver?
Check their cell phones, credit cards?

13:54.917 --> 13:58.580
Clark, the nanosecond that they use
technology, we'll have their number.

13:58.754 --> 14:01.621
Oh. Looks like your get up and 90-90
is long gone.

14:01.841 --> 14:05.208
There's a gang breaking rocks
in my head, but I can make a sentence.

14:05.386 --> 14:07.593
Chloe, do you wanna take this?

14:09.765 --> 14:11.266
No, I think it's in good hands.

14:13.602 --> 14:15.012
So no sign of Oliver.

14:15.187 --> 14:18.554
And I just tried calling
the Chapel of Love, no answer.

14:19.733 --> 14:21.519
I may have one.

14:23.028 --> 14:25.280
An armored car company
that lost a vehicle.

14:25.447 --> 14:28.780
From their security footage,
the same that Emil's accused of stealing.

14:28.951 --> 14:30.111
Can you track this?

14:30.286 --> 14:34.620
Yeah. I can activate the truck's
alarm system remotely, I think.

14:34.874 --> 14:37.786
Clark, listen for a high-pitched tone.

14:42.965 --> 14:48.426
[BEEPING]

14:48.596 --> 14:51.759
-I hear it.
-Yeah, I can too.

14:51.932 --> 14:54.469
You— You're beeping, Clark.

14:55.227 --> 14:56.967
-Uh....
CHLOE: Hmm.

14:57.146 --> 14:58.386
[BEEPING CONTINUES]

15:01.901 --> 15:02.936
Uh--

15:06.655 --> 15:08.691
I got it this time.

15:16.624 --> 15:18.615
[CAR ALARM WAILING]

15:28.969 --> 15:30.345
[TURNS OFF ALARM]

15:48.989 --> 15:51.196
LOIS: The moming-after mind-swipe
was a stinger...

15:51.367 --> 15:53.858
...but the sweet smell of sewage
is clearing my head.

15:54.036 --> 15:55.867
Lois, we're gonna ﬁnd them, okay?

15:56.038 --> 15:58.495
If Clark's with Chloe,
he'll take care of her too.

15:58.666 --> 16:01.874
I know.
I was just checking out my single hand.

16:02.044 --> 16:05.036
-My no-longer-engaged hand.
-Lois, you're still engaged.

16:05.547 --> 16:08.254
You may just have to let go of the ring.
I tell you what.

16:08.425 --> 16:12.794
My corporation, I may have lost it, but I'm
gonna buy you an identical rock, okay?

16:13.097 --> 16:16.214
The last thing I wanna go around with
for the rest of my life...

16:16.392 --> 16:19.350
-...is a lie propagated by my ex-boyfriend.
-Oh.

16:19.520 --> 16:22.933
The ring Clark gave me was a symbol
of our love, of our future together.

16:23.107 --> 16:26.395
It wasn't just any ring, it was the ring.
The big kahuna.

16:26.568 --> 16:29.696
I waited to ﬁnd somebody
who would get this wacky world view...

16:29.863 --> 16:32.570
...and care enough to give me the ring,
and I lose it.

16:32.741 --> 16:34.527
He's gonna understand.
He always does.

16:34.702 --> 16:36.363
We cannot tell Clark.

16:36.537 --> 16:38.869
I'll do whatever it takes
to get that ring back.

16:39.039 --> 16:41.906
Relax, all right?
You're starting to do that twitchy thing.

16:42.084 --> 16:43.745
There's something stuck in my bra--

16:43.919 --> 16:46.410
That's not my territory anymore,
all right?

16:46.588 --> 16:49.250
Cha-ching. Well, that's a ﬁrst.

16:49.591 --> 16:51.627
"Fortune Casino"?

16:51.844 --> 16:53.630
Let me see that.

16:53.846 --> 16:55.086
Oh, look at that.

16:57.266 --> 17:00.258
Your pointer sisters gave us our clue
as to where we were.

17:00.436 --> 17:02.427
-Yeah, right.
-Thank you, sir.

17:02.604 --> 17:05.767
DRIVER: Come on, hop in.
LOIS: Thank you. Oh.

17:08.777 --> 17:10.278
[TYPING]

17:11.447 --> 17:14.780
I can't believe on my ﬁrst
drunken night out I lose Lois...

17:14.950 --> 17:17.657
...commit a felony,
and I land my friend in jail.

17:17.870 --> 17:18.985
So reckless.

17:21.290 --> 17:24.077
But oddly, Clark, very human.

17:24.376 --> 17:26.662
And when this happens
to grooms the world over...

17:26.879 --> 17:29.746
...his friends rally around him
and help make it all right.

17:29.923 --> 17:33.165
Speaking of which, I just found
some very interesting information...

17:33.385 --> 17:35.000
...down at the police station.

17:35.179 --> 17:36.294
NoEmﬂ

17:36.472 --> 17:39.009
And no trace of his name
in any of the police records.

17:41.643 --> 17:43.258
If Emil wasn't arrested...

17:46.648 --> 17:48.775
...who were those cops?

17:49.610 --> 17:50.850
[GRUNTING]

17:54.907 --> 17:55.942
[COUGHS]

17:56.909 --> 17:58.490
Where's the money?

17:59.912 --> 18:02.699
One more Elvis cover out of you...

18:02.915 --> 18:05.281
...and you'll be eating
those blue suede shoes.

18:06.460 --> 18:09.497
I do believe it's fair to say
that you are not the authorities.

18:09.671 --> 18:11.832
And you are not the king of rock.

18:12.007 --> 18:14.999
But you'll be just as dead
if you don't cough up the cash.

18:15.302 --> 18:16.633
[SIGHS]

18:16.804 --> 18:20.171
Listen, I already told you,
you got the wrong Elvis.

18:20.349 --> 18:22.840
|-- I didn't--
I didn't steal any armored car.

18:23.018 --> 18:27.637
No, no, no. I got the right mug.
Yeah.

18:27.815 --> 18:28.850
[CHUCKLES]

18:29.566 --> 18:32.308
It was lady luck
that brought you to me.

18:32.486 --> 18:34.522
I mean, what are the odds, huh?

18:34.696 --> 18:37.654
That you would be
an overnight sensation...

18:37.825 --> 18:41.818
...on the same night
that I was looking for you?

18:43.914 --> 18:45.870
[SPEAKING IN LATIN]

18:46.041 --> 18:47.247
EMIL:
I mean--

18:48.335 --> 18:49.541
It's a fallacy.

18:49.711 --> 18:52.418
Just because the two events
are connected sequentially...

18:52.589 --> 18:56.377
-...doesn't mean they are causally.
-No, no. You are connected, my friend.

18:57.678 --> 19:02.012
I mean, I didn't believe these yahoos
when they told me they were duped...

19:02.182 --> 19:05.549
...but then I saw it for myself.

19:06.520 --> 19:08.101
What?

19:08.730 --> 19:10.186
[REMOTE CONTROL BEEPS]

19:11.275 --> 19:13.732
CHLOE:
A monkey. Hee-hee-hee!

19:16.071 --> 19:17.186
What is this?

19:17.364 --> 19:18.774
EMIL [ON TV]: What you wearing?
MAN: Don't move.

19:19.241 --> 19:21.072
CLARK:
Watch this.

19:21.243 --> 19:23.154
CHLOE: Ta-da!
EMIL: Yeah!

19:23.328 --> 19:24.738
FORTUNE:
It's you.

19:25.539 --> 19:27.245
Here, let me bring it up.

19:28.250 --> 19:30.491
Ahh! Ha-ha-ha.

19:32.254 --> 19:35.746
FORTUNE: Oh, pretty fancy smoke and
mirrors that you pulled off.

19:35.924 --> 19:38.131
It's just-- l--

19:39.136 --> 19:42.094
I don't know what burns me more...

19:42.264 --> 19:46.052
...the fact that you took my money
or the fact that you—

19:46.393 --> 19:49.430
You took my lucky lemur.

19:53.108 --> 19:55.144
It appears to me...

19:55.319 --> 19:58.607
...that someone was trying
to prevent a robbery, not commit one.

20:00.073 --> 20:01.449
Nice masks, boys.

20:04.244 --> 20:05.825
Yeah. Big mistake.

20:06.038 --> 20:09.326
You trying to protect your friends,
smart guy.

20:12.461 --> 20:14.122
Break him.

20:19.301 --> 20:21.292
[CHATTERING AND MACHINES BEEPING]

20:24.014 --> 20:26.676
This $500 baby here means
we were probably gambling.

20:26.850 --> 20:28.511
And knowing you, blackjack, right?

20:28.685 --> 20:32.018
That's my game.
l was three-time champ at Fort Dix.

20:32.814 --> 20:34.475
Oh, my God, what if I bet the ring?

20:34.650 --> 20:36.436
I don't think that would've happened.

20:36.652 --> 20:38.563
I told you
never to come back here again.

20:38.946 --> 20:41.312
No kidding. Huh.

20:41.490 --> 20:43.947
Listen, I got a question for you,
my friend here...

20:44.159 --> 20:46.821
...she lost a ring last night.
Do you have any idea--?

20:46.995 --> 20:49.828
Your little card shark here,
she bet her engagement ring, yeah.

20:49.998 --> 20:52.284
-Oh.
-Did I call it, or did I call it?

20:52.459 --> 20:54.700
She was raking it in,
trash-talking the boss...

20:54.878 --> 20:56.414
...so he won the ring off her.

20:57.172 --> 20:59.128
I don't wanna take you
for another ride.

20:59.299 --> 21:01.631
No, no, wait.
Oliver, this isn't possible.

21:01.802 --> 21:02.882
Not in this lifetime.

21:03.053 --> 21:06.887
The only conceivable way that I would
bet the ring was if it was a sure thing.

21:07.057 --> 21:09.093
No such thing in life as a sure thing.

21:09.559 --> 21:11.811
Oh, yeah? What are you trying to say?

21:12.187 --> 21:13.222
Was I scammed?

21:14.773 --> 21:17.230
Let me guess,
your boss stacked the deck, right?

21:26.827 --> 21:27.862
[INAUDIBLE DIALOGUE]

21:28.996 --> 21:30.031
[SIGHS]

21:30.205 --> 21:32.287
There is no way
I'm gonna let that creep...

21:32.457 --> 21:34.789
...cheat me
out of my happily-forever-after.

21:34.960 --> 21:36.951
-Here comes the bride.
-No.

21:37.129 --> 21:38.460
LOIS: Hey!
-Easy does it.

21:38.630 --> 21:43.715
EMCEE: Please put your hands together
for the Fortune Showgirls.

21:43.885 --> 21:45.045
[SHOW TUNE
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS]

21:45.220 --> 21:46.460
Come with me.

21:46.638 --> 21:48.344
LOIS:
It's all right.

21:58.400 --> 22:03.064
Ahh. l was so close, I could have ripped
my ring off his chubby little ﬁnger.

22:03.238 --> 22:05.820
Not really feeling
yourjewelry malfunction right now.

22:05.991 --> 22:08.482
-It was so much more than that, Oliver.
-I know.

22:08.660 --> 22:12.369
And now, to get out of this poker game,
we need a get-out-of-jail-free card.

22:12.539 --> 22:15.076
-You think?
-You see that pole over there?

22:15.584 --> 22:18.166
-We're going there. Okay?
-A little tied up right now.

22:18.337 --> 22:19.372
[CH UCKLES]

22:19.546 --> 22:21.753
You're a comedienne.
You're gonna lean against me.

22:21.923 --> 22:26.417
All right? And we're gonna shufﬂe
over there in one, two, shufﬂe.

22:26.595 --> 22:28.005
Go, go.

22:28.180 --> 22:31.968
I should have known all this bridal
hoopla was too good to be true.

22:32.142 --> 22:33.928
-Keep working.
-My prenuptial bliss...

22:34.102 --> 22:37.094
...was just one right click away
from bridal apocalypse.

22:37.272 --> 22:39.809
OLIVER:
Oh. Okay.

22:40.108 --> 22:43.600
You should really ease up on yourself,
Lois. You haven't ruined anything.

22:43.779 --> 22:45.110
LOIS:
You still don't get it.

22:46.448 --> 22:50.441
I did not wanna be the bride waving
her freak ﬂag down the aisle, okay?

22:50.619 --> 22:53.986
I wanted this to be perfect.
Not my normal mess.

22:55.499 --> 22:57.785
We're all a mess, okay? Let's be fair.

22:57.959 --> 22:59.039
LOIS:
Not Clark.

22:59.461 --> 23:03.295
No, Clark would never lose his ring.
Okay?

23:03.673 --> 23:05.755
Have any idea
how much pressure there is...

23:05.926 --> 23:08.633
...being engaged
to a walking perfection?

23:10.263 --> 23:11.298
[SIGHS]

23:13.141 --> 23:17.430
You have any idea how much pressure
there is ﬁghting crime next to perfection?

23:17.729 --> 23:19.811
You're free. Let's blow this pop stand.

23:20.357 --> 23:22.018
No. Oh—

23:22.359 --> 23:24.099
We're not leaving without my ring.

23:25.862 --> 23:28.399
I thought we were past that.

23:28.740 --> 23:30.446
Well, we're not.

23:35.664 --> 23:38.952
Oh. Okay. Get back in, get back in.

23:42.421 --> 23:44.537
-You got it? Okay.
-Yeah.

23:56.852 --> 23:58.467
[POUNDING ON DOOR]

23:58.645 --> 23:59.885
We'll be lucky to get out.

24:00.063 --> 24:02.930
I didn't bring my Green Arrow gear
to the bachelor party.

24:05.026 --> 24:06.527
Uh....

24:09.531 --> 24:10.987
Unless....

24:19.624 --> 24:22.457
The facial-recognition
from the security footage showed...

24:22.627 --> 24:25.994
...the fake cops have criminal histories
linking them to this casino.

24:26.173 --> 24:28.915
That is if they work
for this fearless Fortune.

24:29.092 --> 24:31.879
EMCEE:
Fortune Showgirls.

24:32.471 --> 24:34.757
That means Emil could be in danger.

24:37.934 --> 24:41.392
But all I see is a hothouse full
of chumps, suckers and high rollers.

24:41.563 --> 24:44.145
I'll check the other room.
Try to blend in.

24:58.121 --> 24:59.201
Lois.

25:05.629 --> 25:06.789
Oliver?

25:15.639 --> 25:19.632
Give it up for the Fortune Showgirls.

25:21.228 --> 25:24.937
Hey, big daddy.
Wanna give this girl some loving?

25:28.485 --> 25:30.476
Do something.

25:33.031 --> 25:36.023
Well, luck be a lady tonight.

25:36.368 --> 25:38.108
You are an eyeful.

25:38.286 --> 25:41.653
You know, like the tower in Paris.

25:42.290 --> 25:44.576
You put these other hothouse girls
to shame.

25:45.835 --> 25:47.496
Thanks, man.

25:54.844 --> 25:56.630
That's her. The blond!

25:58.139 --> 25:59.879
One of the crew
that stole the money.

26:00.058 --> 26:01.264
Chloe, run!

26:05.981 --> 26:07.812
-Get her! Get her!
-Hey.

26:33.592 --> 26:34.923
Yes!

27:02.245 --> 27:04.452
Yes. Come to mama, sweetheart.

27:06.207 --> 27:07.538
Come on.

27:28.438 --> 27:32.181
Oh. There's my sparkly girl.

27:32.359 --> 27:33.644
Come to mama.

27:33.818 --> 27:36.651
I swear I will never bet you again.

27:40.200 --> 27:42.942
You think I'm gonna let you run off
with my lucky ring?

27:43.119 --> 27:45.781
I won so big today.

27:45.955 --> 27:50.073
The only one getting lucky here tonight
is yours truly.

27:56.466 --> 27:59.082
-Way to go all in, gorgeous.
-Back at you, hot stuff.

27:59.260 --> 28:01.672
And we have a winner.

28:08.228 --> 28:10.469
Wait, wait, wait.
I told you, gentlemen...

28:10.647 --> 28:12.979
...I don't remember anything.
It's all a blank.

28:13.149 --> 28:15.731
Yeah, you did,
but, you see, that's what they all say.

28:15.902 --> 28:19.941
In the end, everybody names names.
It's just the business.

28:20.115 --> 28:21.821
Business?

28:22.117 --> 28:23.573
Wait a minute, that's it.

28:23.743 --> 28:27.156
That's why Fortune
had you robbing his truck.

28:28.123 --> 28:30.739
No, if my calculations are correct,
it's a scam. Right?

28:30.917 --> 28:34.626
He reports the crime, and then the
insurance company doubles his money.

28:34.796 --> 28:39.210
Except this time,
somebody actually stole his money.

28:39.676 --> 28:41.632
Yeah, that was you, smart guy.

28:42.637 --> 28:45.674
Oh, I really wish I didn't understand
the physics of this.

28:45.849 --> 28:47.134
[GRUNTING]

28:49.894 --> 28:51.885
[SCREAMING]

29:08.246 --> 29:09.406
[EMIL GROANS]

29:11.833 --> 29:14.290
-Are you all right?
EMIL: Clark.

29:16.045 --> 29:17.785
Clark.

29:18.173 --> 29:19.629
You're safe now.

29:19.799 --> 29:23.007
Look, I need some answers
about what happened last night.

29:27.724 --> 29:29.715
Get in line.

29:40.069 --> 29:41.650
CLARK:
Chloe?

29:47.160 --> 29:50.243
Congratulations on surviving
your boffo bachelor party...

29:51.664 --> 29:54.201
...and the million-dollar
morning-after mistake.

29:55.752 --> 29:58.869
There's still one thing we have do.
Well, undo.

29:59.422 --> 30:01.754
I got through to the chapel
and they told me...

30:01.925 --> 30:04.291
...the friend masquerading
as the bride-to-be...

30:04.469 --> 30:06.755
...was just a drunk prank, so....

30:07.222 --> 30:09.679
-That's a relief.
-Yeah.

30:11.976 --> 30:14.353
It was a fun ride while it lasted.

30:14.521 --> 30:16.477
Kind of reminded me
of the good old days.

30:16.648 --> 30:19.765
Yeah, but your new partner-in-crime's
got you covered.

30:23.279 --> 30:25.895
Lois and I are pretty good together.

30:28.868 --> 30:32.076
It's funny, it almost sounded
like you were saying goodbye.

30:35.917 --> 30:37.623
I forget how well you know me.

30:38.753 --> 30:41.961
My heart and my head
have been playing tug-of-war lately.

30:43.800 --> 30:45.961
But I made my decision.

30:47.971 --> 30:52.180
l have to break it to Oliver, but I won't
let a hero give up his world for me.

30:52.350 --> 30:54.716
Chloe, you just got back.

30:55.311 --> 30:57.176
You're the heart and soul
of Watchtower.

30:57.355 --> 31:00.722
Yeah,
but I can't be Watchtower anymore.

31:00.900 --> 31:03.516
I've already been the ghost
in the machine once...

31:03.695 --> 31:05.731
...I can't do it again.

31:05.947 --> 31:09.155
You know you've always been
much more than that to me.

31:11.870 --> 31:13.576
I know.

31:14.414 --> 31:18.953
In every epic tale there's always
one person who believes in the hero ﬁrst.

31:19.377 --> 31:23.086
Someone who helps inspire them
to greatness.

31:24.382 --> 31:27.294
You know,
maybe it wasn't just a ﬂuke with you.

31:27.677 --> 31:29.884
I've been thinking
that's my true calling.

31:30.054 --> 31:32.045
Finding heroes
and helping them realize...

31:32.223 --> 31:35.511
...their true potential
beyond the reach of Watchtower.

31:39.147 --> 31:41.229
You're not alone, Clark Kent.

31:42.984 --> 31:46.977
In all my globetrotting
l have met several others like you.

31:48.823 --> 31:50.688
A billionaire with high-tech toys...

31:50.867 --> 31:54.485
...and a wondrous woman
who is gonna throw you for a loop.

31:54.954 --> 31:57.366
Well, all that sounds amazing...

31:58.875 --> 32:00.786
...and a bit lonely.

32:00.960 --> 32:05.329
Well, that's why
I'm following your lead, Clark.

32:06.466 --> 32:09.754
I've created a double identity
for myself.

32:11.763 --> 32:14.596
You're looking
at the Star City Register's newest hire.

32:16.559 --> 32:18.345
By day, of course.

32:30.490 --> 32:33.857
| always knew that you were destined
for big things, Chloe.

32:37.789 --> 32:41.452
And I know, no matter what,
we'll still be in each other's lives.

32:42.001 --> 32:44.162
You know I'll always be here for you.

32:49.384 --> 32:51.124
You know that, right?

32:51.552 --> 32:53.292
I do.

32:57.600 --> 32:59.056
[CH UCKLES]

33:11.864 --> 33:13.946
Hey, hound dog.

33:14.575 --> 33:16.736
You really rocked this town.

33:16.911 --> 33:19.323
I suppose
that's supposed to be humorous?

33:19.497 --> 33:21.408
It's just--

33:21.624 --> 33:23.330
Well, it was a nice surprise...

33:23.501 --> 33:28.712
...to see our mild-mannered doctor
have a special power of his own.

33:31.384 --> 33:33.591
I haven't done something like that
since--

33:33.761 --> 33:37.345
Well, since my wife passed away.

33:39.475 --> 33:41.887
She used to love
to hear me sing to her.

33:42.061 --> 33:44.052
[TYPING]

33:46.107 --> 33:47.893
Don't give it up.

33:50.820 --> 33:53.061
She wouldn't have wanted you to.

33:56.117 --> 33:57.448
[DOOR OPENS]

33:57.660 --> 33:59.946
All right. Listen up.
l have the smoking gun.

34:00.121 --> 34:02.908
I haven't laid eyes on the footage yet
but I suspect...

34:03.082 --> 34:06.620
...that inside this little puppy are
the answers to our burning questions.

34:06.794 --> 34:10.286
-My camera. Of course. I forgot I that l--
TESS: Ahem. This looks really damaged.

34:10.465 --> 34:12.831
--was documenting the entire evening.

34:13.009 --> 34:15.091
OLIVER: See if we can play this thing.
-Maybe—

34:15.261 --> 34:18.594
I found it in a puddle of champagne
in the limo.

34:18.765 --> 34:20.630
You know what we should do?
Champagne.

34:21.100 --> 34:22.385
-No, no.
TESS: Absolutely not.

34:23.019 --> 34:24.975
There's sparkling cider in the fridge...

34:25.146 --> 34:28.309
...which I am certain
Zatanna has not charmed.

34:30.610 --> 34:32.316
TESS:
We got this.

34:33.112 --> 34:35.524
CLARK: I got it.
-Oh.

34:54.175 --> 34:57.759
Uh-- I'm so gun shy,
I don't even know if I can try it.

34:59.514 --> 35:01.596
Here's the thing, Clark. I, uh....

35:03.726 --> 35:05.057
I bet the ring.

35:05.228 --> 35:07.594
I mean, I got it back, but....

35:08.773 --> 35:10.104
Please forgive me.

35:11.818 --> 35:14.400
Lois, there's nothing to forgive.

35:16.405 --> 35:18.987
The ring is not what's important.

35:20.493 --> 35:21.699
You are.

35:26.249 --> 35:29.241
But I have a bit
of a confession myself.

35:30.962 --> 35:32.623
When I woke up
and you were gone...

35:32.797 --> 35:35.379
...I thought that I'd scared you away
somehow.

35:36.968 --> 35:41.007
Yeah, I'm sorry, I know that l have
the runaway girlfriend thing to--

35:41.180 --> 35:44.547
Look, if all this wedding mess
is getting to be too much, then--

35:44.725 --> 35:46.636
No, it's not that.

35:46.811 --> 35:48.301
It's...

35:48.646 --> 35:49.806
...hard to explain.

35:49.981 --> 35:51.596
You don't need to explain.

35:53.151 --> 35:55.312
| just want you to know...

35:56.362 --> 35:58.398
...that if you're having doubts inside...

35:58.573 --> 36:02.282
...or you're not 100 percent sure
that this is the right thing to do...

36:02.660 --> 36:04.366
...I will understand.

36:08.457 --> 36:12.826
I'm gonna wanna marry you
in ﬁve days or in ﬁve years.

36:16.591 --> 36:18.707
That was the perfect thing to say.

36:23.764 --> 36:26.221
Oh, and we're rolling.

36:30.897 --> 36:33.889
File's corrupted,
but we'll see what we've got.

36:38.070 --> 36:39.981
Ready for this?

36:40.740 --> 36:44.107
LOIS [ON TV]: Clark!
CLARK: Sorry, you said you were cold.

36:44.285 --> 36:45.821
Hey, uh...

36:46.621 --> 36:49.784
...Lois, if you're watching this
20 years from now...

36:49.957 --> 36:52.289
...just know
that you are the love of my life.

36:52.793 --> 36:55.660
[CLARK & LOIS LAUGH ON TV]

36:55.838 --> 36:58.830
Uh- I'm really feeling this.

36:59.926 --> 37:02.759
TESS:
Mm. Mm. You- Oh!

37:03.346 --> 37:06.179
Alcohol doesn't even affect me.

37:06.349 --> 37:10.262
[LAUGHING ON TV]

37:12.146 --> 37:13.807
EMIL:
That's not what I was imagining.

37:13.981 --> 37:15.937
[GROUP LAUGHING ON TV]

37:16.108 --> 37:18.724
-Hey, Emil.
-Merry Christmas. Drink it.

37:18.903 --> 37:20.359
Drink it. Drink it.

37:20.529 --> 37:21.939
CHLOE:
Oh, my God.

37:22.114 --> 37:25.072
-I mean, are you really made of steel?
CHLOE: Emil.

37:25.576 --> 37:26.907
LOIS: Oh!
-Aah!

37:27.245 --> 37:28.325
CHLOE:
That was not-

37:28.496 --> 37:29.781
CHLOE: Ha-ha-ha.
LOIS: Whoo!

37:30.498 --> 37:34.161
-Oh, this is good. How about this one?
-Well, we 're two different-

37:34.335 --> 37:36.166
You're not thinking this through.
Okay?

37:36.337 --> 37:39.124
These are- What the--?
How much did this cost you?

37:39.340 --> 37:41.422
-Nothing.
-That's a woman's ring. All right?

37:41.592 --> 37:43.093
Rings out of a vending machine.

37:43.261 --> 37:46.173
She deserves better than that.

37:46.347 --> 37:47.837
Right?

37:48.724 --> 37:52.592
How about a little privacy there,
Blair Witch? Now.

37:53.062 --> 37:55.599
I wouldn't be caught dead
in that thing.

37:56.148 --> 37:58.685
TESS: Beautiful.
-Looks so nice. Thank you so much.

37:58.859 --> 38:00.770
-I need your help.
-Okay. Shh.

38:00.945 --> 38:03.982
CHLOE:
Oliver? Where are you going?

38:04.490 --> 38:05.855
What? Ha-ha-ha.

38:07.743 --> 38:08.778
Yes.

38:09.161 --> 38:11.777
-You know what, l-- I can't--
-No, no. Stay.

38:11.956 --> 38:13.992
EMIL: Bravo, sir.
-Monkey.

38:14.166 --> 38:16.157
CHLOE:
Monkey?

38:18.087 --> 38:20.499
A monkey. Hee-hee-hee!

38:20.673 --> 38:22.038
Oh!

38:22.633 --> 38:24.624
GUIDO: Hey. Don't move.
EMIL: What are you wearing?

38:24.802 --> 38:26.303
GUIDO:
Don't move.

38:27.096 --> 38:28.927
Watch this.

38:30.099 --> 38:32.681
CHLOE: Ta-da!
EMIL: Yeah!

38:32.893 --> 38:35.635
TESS: Clark saves the day.
-All right, all right. Here we go.

38:35.813 --> 38:37.144
Check it out. Check it out.

38:37.315 --> 38:39.146
I 'd like to introduce you to somebody.

38:39.900 --> 38:44.269
EMIL: What's his name?
CLARK: This is, uh- The doctor-

38:44.905 --> 38:46.987
CHLOE: Who?
EMIL: The lemur.

38:47.158 --> 38:50.321
Let me tell you something, Tess.
Let me tell you something.

38:50.494 --> 38:53.406
lMth being the king
comes a lot of responsibility.

38:53.581 --> 38:56.288
Uneasy lies the head
that wears the crown.

38:56.459 --> 38:57.915
You know what I'm saying?

38:58.085 --> 38:59.916
[WOMEN LAUGHING ON TV]

39:01.756 --> 39:03.212
[LAUGHS]

39:05.426 --> 39:06.541
[EMIL CHUCKLES ON TV]

39:06.719 --> 39:08.505
OLIVER: Oh, look at you.
-Oh, no.

39:08.679 --> 39:09.964
EMIL:
Don't be coy.

39:10.723 --> 39:12.509
No, no, no.

39:12.683 --> 39:14.594
WOMAN: What you got?
-Oh, you can't handle what I got.

39:14.769 --> 39:15.804
[GRUNTING]

39:15.978 --> 39:17.058
WOMAN:
Yeah!

39:17.229 --> 39:18.844
[WOMAN LAUGHS ON TV]

39:19.023 --> 39:20.809
[LAUGHS ON TV]

39:20.983 --> 39:23.770
Cut it out, get over here, baby doll.
See what you got. Oh.

39:23.944 --> 39:27.732
Oh, don't be coy, honey. Come on.
Give me some--

39:27.948 --> 39:30.200
-Okay. Okay.
EMIL: Oh, yeah.

39:30.368 --> 39:32.108
-Okay, okay.
-Maybe now would be--

39:32.286 --> 39:35.244
OLIVER: Hey, hey, hey. No, no.
EMIL: A good time to hit the power button.

39:35.456 --> 39:37.492
-You know where the power button is?
-Yeah.

39:37.666 --> 39:40.203
OLIVER: That's great stuff.
I'm real proud of you.

39:40.378 --> 39:43.290
EMIL: Do you know where the power--?
Do you know where the power--?

39:43.547 --> 39:45.538
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

39:50.846 --> 39:52.347
OLIVER:
Hey.

39:57.978 --> 40:00.640
Where you running off to so quick?

40:03.484 --> 40:04.849
What are you doing?

40:05.027 --> 40:07.689
I thought we were rendezvousing
at your place later.

40:11.992 --> 40:14.483
You're leaving again, right?

40:18.624 --> 40:22.333
-Oliver, l--
-lt's okay, I can read between the lines.

40:28.843 --> 40:31.835
Chloe, I never expected you
to sit up in that Watchtower...

40:32.012 --> 40:33.843
...for the rest of your life.

40:34.140 --> 40:36.096
I know better than that.

40:40.020 --> 40:41.681
l have something— Wait.

41:05.796 --> 41:07.912
I don't know what you're thinking...

41:10.176 --> 41:13.543
...but I hope it's not that you're
gonna run off without your husband.

41:16.348 --> 41:18.885
I hope you didn't take a job
in my hometown for nothing.

41:19.059 --> 41:20.390
[LAUGHS]

41:30.988 --> 41:32.353
Let's get out of here.

42:13.531 --> 42:15.522
[English - US - SDH]
